io.afero.sdk.device

Class DeviceModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.afero.sdk.device.DeviceModel

  • public final class DeviceModel
extends Object
    This class manages the attribute state and events associated with a particular instance of an Afero peripheral device.

      • writeAttributes

        public AttributeWriter writeAttributes()
        Writes new values to one or more device attributes. When the operation completes successfully the new values have been confirmed by the physical device. It is possible for some of the attribute writes to succeed and others to fail.

        Example: 

        
     deviceModel.writeAttributes()
         .put(powerAttrId, powerValue)
         .put(modeAttrId, modeValue)
         .commit()
         .subscribe(new Observer<AttributeWriter.Result>() {
              @Override
              public void onNext(AttributeWriter.Result result) {
                  if (result.isSuccess()) {
                      // the physical device confirmed the write
                  } else {
                      // the write for one of the attributes failed
                  }
              }

              @Override
              public void onError(Throwable t) {
                   // call failed, log the error
                   AfLog.e(t);
              }

              @Override
              public void onCompleted() {
                  // write operation completed
              }
         });

        Returns:
        AttributeWriter that is used to compose, initiate, and monitor the write operation.
        See Also:
        AttributeWriter
